---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/global/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Services', href: '/services' },
  { name: 'Behaviour Planning', href: '/services/behaviour-planning' }
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Behaviour Support Planning | Rabbia Psychologist" description="Online behaviour support planning for tantrums, meltdowns, refusal, aggression, and daily routine struggles.">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 max-w-4xl">
    <Breadcrumbs paths={breadcrumbs} />

    <div class="mt-8 mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">Behaviour Planning Session</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700">A structured approach to understanding the 'why' behind tantrums, meltdowns, defiance, and refusal, and building a parent response plan.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy">Behaviour is Communication</h2>
      <p>Children do not want to be "bad." Challenging behaviour is almost always a sign that a child is lacking the skills to handle a situation, or they are trying to communicate an unmet need (like escaping a demand, seeking connection, or sensory overload).</p>

      <p>Our approach starts with decoding the behaviour rather than just trying to punish it away.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy">Tantrum vs. Meltdown</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-6">
        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-blue-100">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mt-0">A Tantrum is...</h4>
          <p class="text-sm">Usually goal-oriented. The child wants something (a toy, attention) or wants to avoid something. They are still somewhat in control and will often stop if they get what they want.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-red-100">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mt-0">A Meltdown is...</h4>
          <p class="text-sm">A neurological response to being completely overwhelmed (sensory, emotional, cognitive). The child has lost control and cannot be reasoned with. They need safety and co-regulation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy">Common Parent Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Talking too much or trying to reason with a child during a meltdown.</li>
        <li>Focusing only on the consequence, rather than what triggered the behaviour.</li>
        <li>Being inconsistent with boundaries.</li>
        <li>Reacting with big emotions, which escalates the child further.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy">What a Session Includes</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
        <table class="min-w-full bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm rounded-lg">
          <thead class="bg-gray-50">
            <tr>
              <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left font-semibold text-brand-navy border-b border-gray-200">Step</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left font-semibold text-brand-navy border-b border-gray-200">Focus</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 border-b border-gray-100">Trigger Review</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 border-b border-gray-100">Identifying the hidden antecedents (what happens right before).</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 border-b border-gray-100">Pattern Mapping</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 border-b border-gray-100">Using the <a href="/free-downloads" class="text-brand-trust">ABC Tracker</a> to uncover the 'why'.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 border-b border-gray-100">Parent Response Plan</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 border-b border-gray-100">Exactly what to say and do in the moment to de-escalate.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Proactive Steps</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Home changes to prevent the behaviour from happening in the first place.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 mt-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-brand-navy">Is my child present for this session?</h4>
        <p>No. This is a parent-only session. We focus on giving <em>you</em> the tools to manage the environment and your responses.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-brand-cream p-8 rounded-xl border border-brand-gold mt-12 text-center">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Stop the cycle of stress and yelling.</h3>
        <p class="mb-6">Book a Behaviour Planning Session (USD 95 / AUD 145).</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="/book" class="bg-brand-navy text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-bold hover:bg-blue-900 transition-colors">Book Behaviour Planning</a>
          <a href="/pricing" class="bg-white text-brand-navy border-2 border-brand-navy px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-bold hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">View All Pricing</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
